<DocsLayout
  title="Datagen CLI Reference"
  description="Complete reference for datagen CLI commands"
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  headings={headings}
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>

  <p>
    The <code>datagen</code> CLI is a tool for generating realistic test data based on model
    definitions written in the datagen DSL.
  </p>

  <h2 id="commands">Commands</h2>

  <h3>datagen generate</h3>

  <p>Generate data from model files.</p>

  <pre><code>datagen generate &lt;model-file&gt; [flags]</code></pre>

  <h4>Flags</h4>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Flag</th>
        <th>Short</th>
        <th>Default</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--count</code></td>
        <td><code>-c</code></td>
        <td><code>10</code></td>
        <td>Number of records to generate</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--output</code></td>
        <td><code>-o</code></td>
        <td><code>stdout</code></td>
        <td>Output file path</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--format</code></td>
        <td><code>-f</code></td>
        <td><code>json</code></td>
        <td>Output format (json, csv, sql)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h4>Examples</h4>

  <pre><code># Generate 100 records
datagen generate users.dg --count 100

# Output to file
datagen generate users.dg --count 1000 --output users.json

# Generate CSV format
datagen generate users.dg --format csv --output users.csv</code></pre>

  <h3>datagen validate</h3>

  <p>Validate model file syntax.</p>

  <pre><code>datagen validate &lt;model-file&gt;</code></pre>

  <h3>datagen version</h3>

  <p>Show datagen version.</p>

  <pre><code>datagen version</code></pre>

  <h2 id="global-flags">Global Flags</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Flag</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
